annotationA: Birt-Hogg-Dube homolog; It is involved in the biological process described with: negative regulation of transcription of nuclear large rRNA transcript from RNA polymerase I promoter; germ-line stem cell maintenance; negative regulation of RNA polymerase I regulatory region sequence-specific DNA binding
annotationB: Ragulator complex protein LAMTOR2 homolog; Regulator of the TOR pathway, a signaling cascade that promotes cell growth in response to growth factors, energy levels, and amino acids. As part of the Ragulator complex, may activate the TOR signaling cascade in response to amino acids
